ENTRY            F1535   20251210   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1535001   20251210   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 11         30
TITLE      Experimental studies of 10B(7Li,6Li)11B and
           10B(7Li,6He)11C transfer reactions at 58 MeV
AUTHOR     (Yu.G.Sobolev,J.L.Ferreira,S.S.Stukalov,
           Yu.E.Penionzhkevich,N.Burtebayev,A.N.Danilov,
           A.S.Demyanova,S.V.Dmitriev,Yu.B.Gurov,M.Nassurlla,
           V.I.Starastsin,A.V.Shakhov,J.Lubian)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,3BZLUFF,4KASKAZ,4RUSKUR)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,112,064601,2025)
           #doi:10.1103/z18g-bc84
           (J,PAN,87,S426,2024) Data for Li-6 are given.
           #doi:10.1134/S1063778824701011
FACILITY   (ISOCY,4ZZZDUB) U-400 cyclotron
SAMPLE     A self-supporting 10B target (thickness ~ 0.05 mg/cm2,
           diam. =1.0 cm), containing impurities of 12C (~9%)
           and 16O (~6%), placed inside the reaction chamber,
           perpendicular to the beam axis, was used.
METHOD     (BCINT)
DETECTOR   (SI,TELES) Two detector groups were used. Each group
           consisted of four deltaE -E Si-detector telescopes.
           The first group, with 100 mu-m deltaE detectors and
           3000 mu-m E Si(Li) detectors, measured particles
           emitted at forward angles 7 <theta< 30 degrees. The
           second group consisted of 30 mu-m and 800 mu-m thick
           deltaE and E detectors for reaction-product
           measurements at the angular range 17 <theta< 50 degrees
ADD-RES    The measured differential cross sections were analyzed
           using the finite-range-coupled reaction-channel
           approach.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No source of uncertainty is given
HISTORY    (20251210C)
ENDBIB              30
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
        58.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           37
